Educational Cybersecurity Project

This repository is intended solely for educational and research purposes.

The goal of this project is to demonstrate how keyboard event capture,
multithreading, local socket communication, and basic logging mechanisms
work in Python.

This project was intentionally designed without persistence,
privilege escalation, stealth, antivirus evasion, remote control,
or other techniques commonly associated with real-world malware.

Any use of this code outside of controlled educational environments
is the sole responsibility of the user.

